$ V8: Torsional mode driven by CONM2 CM inertia (i11)
$ Massless 1-element cantilever. Only Rx free at tip.
$ Analytical: k_tor = GJ/L = 1.0*2.0/1.0 = 2.0; I_eff = i11 = 2.0
$             omega = sqrt(2/2) = 1.0 rad/s  ->  f = 1/(2*pi) ~= 0.15915 Hz
SOL 103

SUBCASE 1
  TITLE = CONM2 torsional inertia
  SPC = 1
  METHOD = 20

BEGIN BULK

$ EIGRL: extract 1 mode, MASS normalisation
EIGRL, 20, , , 1, , , , MASS

$ Nodes
GRID, 1, , 0.0, 0.0, 0.0
GRID, 2, , 1.0, 0.0, 0.0

$ E=2.0, G=1.0, nu=0.0, rho=0.0 (massless beam; only torsion matters)
MAT1, 1, 2.0, 1.0, 0.0, 0.0

$ A=0.01 (dummy), I1/I2 small (bending DOFs are SPCed), J=2.0 (torsional constant)
PBAR, 1, 1, 0.01, 0.001, 0.001, 2.0

$ CBAR along X, v-vector in Z
CBAR, 1, 1, 1, 2, 0.0, 0.0, 1.0

$ Fix all 6 DOFs at node 1
SPC1, 1, 123456, 1
$ Fix all DOFs EXCEPT Rx (DOF 4) at node 2: fix DOFs 1,2,3,5,6
SPC1, 1, 12356, 2

$ CONM2: m=0.001 (tiny translational mass; SPCed DOFs), i11=2.0 (torsional inertia)
$ Free-field order: EID, GID, CID, M, X1, X2, X3, I11
CONM2, 1, 2, 0, 0.001, 0.0, 0.0, 0.0, 2.0

ENDDATA
